1
00:00:03,045 --> 00:00:05,547
[theme music plays]

2
00:01:29,172 --> 00:01:32,259
I can't believe my son
is looking at those magazines.

3
00:01:32,634 --> 00:01:33,719
Hey, Light.

4
00:01:33,885 --> 00:01:35,053
Come on!

5
00:01:35,137 --> 00:01:36,847
Dinner's ready!

6
00:01:41,518 --> 00:01:43,478
[Light laughing]

7
00:01:43,854 --> 00:01:45,939
I'll solve equations with my right hand...

8
00:01:46,773 --> 00:01:47,724
SUSPECT: TAYOSHI MURAO

9
00:01:47,862 --> 00:01:49,109
...and write names with my left.

10
00:01:49,276 --> 00:01:50,861
I'll take a potato chip

11
00:01:51,820 --> 00:01:53,363
and eat it.

12
00:01:54,197 --> 00:01:55,741
And the witness to my alibi

13
00:01:56,283 --> 00:01:57,909
is L himself.

14
00:01:58,368 --> 00:02:01,288
ENCOUNTER

15
00:02:02,914 --> 00:02:05,000
Are you sure about this? Ryuk?

16
00:02:05,417 --> 00:02:07,836
Yeah. I'm sure
nobody's following you, okay?

17
00:02:09,755 --> 00:02:11,423
[Ryuk] Now, hurry up already, will ya?

18
00:02:11,632 --> 00:02:13,050
The symptoms are getting worse.

19
00:02:13,508 --> 00:02:16,261
[Light] I really hope you're not saying
what you think I'd want to hear

20
00:02:16,386 --> 00:02:17,638
just to get some apples.

21
00:02:17,721 --> 00:02:19,097
[Ryuk] Whoa. Hold it right there.

22
00:02:19,181 --> 00:02:21,850
I just flew out and checked
a one-hundred-meter radius around you

23
00:02:22,017 --> 00:02:23,143
and there was no one there.

24
00:02:23,226 --> 00:02:25,062
So, yeah, for the last time, I'm sure.
Okay?

25
00:02:25,562 --> 00:02:26,855
All right, but on the news

26
00:02:26,938 --> 00:02:30,317
they said they were dispatching
1,500 investigators to Japan.

27
00:02:30,525 --> 00:02:32,778
They're bluffing.
You said so yourself.

28
00:02:32,903 --> 00:02:35,447
If it were really happening,
they wouldn't announce their arrival.

29
00:02:35,530 --> 00:02:37,366
Instead, they'd come
and investigate secretly.

30
00:02:37,449 --> 00:02:38,450
[Ryuk chuckles nervously]

31
00:02:38,533 --> 00:02:39,993
I suppose you're right.

32
00:02:40,202 --> 00:02:41,828
Well then, I'll buy you some apples.

33
00:02:42,245 --> 00:02:43,288
Nice!

34
00:02:43,455 --> 00:02:44,706
[Ryuk chuckles]

35
00:02:44,831 --> 00:02:46,583
Here you are. Please, come again.

36
00:02:46,833 --> 00:02:48,794
Light, come on! Hurry up!

37
00:02:53,548 --> 00:02:54,841
[chomping loudly]

38
00:02:54,966 --> 00:02:57,719
You know, you're really haven't been
that nice to me.

39
00:02:58,720 --> 00:03:00,514
[chomping]

40
00:03:01,306 --> 00:03:02,432
[swallows]

41
00:03:02,557 --> 00:03:04,851
You have me looking all over for cameras,

42
00:03:04,935 --> 00:03:07,270
telling me that I can't even eat apples
in the house anymore.

43
00:03:07,437 --> 00:03:08,522
It's not right.

44
00:03:08,605 --> 00:03:09,815
-[chains jangle]
-[bones crackle]

45
00:03:10,357 --> 00:03:11,858
Make sure you eat the core as well.

46
00:03:11,983 --> 00:03:13,193
[Ryuk chomping]

47
00:03:14,986 --> 00:03:18,573
You know, I might actually write your name
in my Death Note and kill you.

48
00:03:18,699 --> 00:03:19,825
Just like that.

49
00:03:19,950 --> 00:03:21,326
[Light chuckles]

50
00:03:21,410 --> 00:03:22,828
I wouldn't laugh, if I were you.

51
00:03:22,994 --> 00:03:24,371
[Light] Right. That reminds me

52
00:03:24,705 --> 00:03:26,581
I've got one finishing touch left to add.

53
00:03:28,291 --> 00:03:30,335
Hmm. Hey, Ryuzaki.

54
00:03:30,585 --> 00:03:31,461
[Ryuzaki] Yes?

55
00:03:31,628 --> 00:03:32,587
I've been thinking

56
00:03:32,671 --> 00:03:35,298
about purse-snatcher and embezzler's
heart attacks two days ago.

57
00:03:35,549 --> 00:03:39,386
It seems my family couldn't have had
any knowledge of them before they died.

58
00:03:39,678 --> 00:03:41,471
Shouldn't that resolve
any doubts you have?

59
00:03:42,097 --> 00:03:43,432
You may be right.

60
00:03:43,640 --> 00:03:46,268
Even though Kira can control
the time of death,

61
00:03:46,435 --> 00:03:49,396
I don't think that there's any way
he could've arranged their deaths

62
00:03:49,521 --> 00:03:51,481
without having seen
the broadcast first. Huh?

63
00:03:53,066 --> 00:03:54,693
Your son has come home.

64
00:03:55,277 --> 00:03:56,236
Hmm.

65
00:03:59,948 --> 00:04:03,702
Heh, so you're gonna keep quiet
and pretend to study again, huh?

66
00:04:06,079 --> 00:04:08,707
I have a good grasp
of where all the cameras are placed.

67
00:04:08,874 --> 00:04:11,543
But I only managed to kill
a purse-snatcher and an embezzler...

68
00:04:11,668 --> 00:04:12,544
MURAO TA...

69
00:04:12,627 --> 00:04:13,920
...using that trick with potato chips.

70
00:04:14,629 --> 00:04:16,715
Both of them were guilty
of much lesser crimes

71
00:04:16,882 --> 00:04:18,550
than my previous victims.

72
00:04:18,759 --> 00:04:19,885
[male newscaster] Next in...

73
00:04:20,051 --> 00:04:21,386
You're watching TV?

74
00:04:22,471 --> 00:04:25,390
I made sure to kill criminals
whose names and faces were broadcasted

75
00:04:25,515 --> 00:04:28,101
when I didn't have access
to TV or the Internet.

76
00:04:28,268 --> 00:04:30,437
But there is a chance
I'll look even more suspicious

77
00:04:30,562 --> 00:04:32,689
of only these lesser criminals
end up dying

78
00:04:32,814 --> 00:04:34,566
when I'm not receiving information.

79
00:04:34,733 --> 00:04:35,692
In other words,

80
00:04:35,817 --> 00:04:37,152
if I kill other petty criminals

81
00:04:37,277 --> 00:04:40,113
whose names and faces
are broadcast as I watch TV,

82
00:04:40,322 --> 00:04:42,991
I won't draw
unnecessary attention to myself.

83
00:04:43,533 --> 00:04:44,951
For this to work

84
00:04:45,035 --> 00:04:48,038
all I really have to do is remember
the identities of the criminals

85
00:04:48,163 --> 00:04:50,207
I either see on TV or while I'm online,

86
00:04:50,457 --> 00:04:52,709
regardless of the severity
of their crimes.

87
00:04:53,293 --> 00:04:54,711
That way, whenever I go out...

88
00:04:54,795 --> 00:04:55,879
MAINICHI ASAJ...

89
00:04:55,962 --> 00:04:58,173
...I can use that piece of the Death Note
I keep in my wallet

90
00:04:58,256 --> 00:05:00,091
to kill them at random times.

91
00:05:00,217 --> 00:05:01,510
Just like that.

92
00:05:01,927 --> 00:05:05,013
It's the perfect way
to deal with these hidden cameras.

93
00:05:08,725 --> 00:05:10,101
[Ryuzaki] In the past few days,

94
00:05:10,268 --> 00:05:12,646
I have listened
to all of our audio recordings

95
00:05:12,771 --> 00:05:14,648
and reviewed the video footage
we captured.

96
00:05:14,773 --> 00:05:16,858
I've gone over them many times.

97
00:05:17,317 --> 00:05:19,027
And I've come to a conclusion.

98
00:05:19,110 --> 00:05:21,655
Our surveillance
of the Kitamura and Yagami households,

99
00:05:21,780 --> 00:05:23,156
has revealed...

100
00:05:24,908 --> 00:05:25,992
nothing.

101
00:05:26,743 --> 00:05:28,203
-[Ryuzaki] Hm...
-[sighs]

102
00:05:28,370 --> 00:05:30,455
[Ryuzaki] We will remove
the cameras and wiretaps.

103
00:05:30,997 --> 00:05:31,957
[sighs]

104
00:05:32,165 --> 00:05:34,960
All that and we still
don't have any suspects.

105
00:05:35,210 --> 00:05:36,336
It's okay, Matsuda.

106
00:05:36,419 --> 00:05:38,588
We'll have to pursue other leads
but we'll get them.

107
00:05:38,713 --> 00:05:40,674
[Ryuzaki] Please,
don't get the wrong idea.

108
00:05:42,092 --> 00:05:45,303
I only said that we were unable
to reveal anything suspicious

109
00:05:45,470 --> 00:05:46,805
based on our surveillance.

110
00:05:47,055 --> 00:05:47,931
What?

111
00:05:48,139 --> 00:05:50,350
[Ryuzaki] Even if Kira was among them,

112
00:05:50,559 --> 00:05:52,143
I'm sure he wouldn't make it obvious.

113
00:05:52,310 --> 00:05:55,355
No, in fact, it could mean
he was able to continue killing

114
00:05:55,522 --> 00:05:58,191
without doing anything
outwardly suspicious.

115
00:05:59,401 --> 00:06:03,530
Well, then you believe that Kira
is among one of those families?

116
00:06:04,406 --> 00:06:05,323
As I've said,

117
00:06:06,283 --> 00:06:07,951
there's a five percent chance.

118
00:06:11,705 --> 00:06:13,748
Kira never stopped killing people,

119
00:06:13,832 --> 00:06:16,251
even while the surveillance cameras
were in place.

120
00:06:17,669 --> 00:06:21,423
I still have no idea how he's been able
to commit these murders, but...

121
00:06:22,132 --> 00:06:25,927
let's say he could kill someone
simply by wishing death upon them.

122
00:06:26,011 --> 00:06:28,889
You'd think that any human being
would have shown at least some emotion,

123
00:06:29,055 --> 00:06:31,892
some sign that they were knowingly
committing an act of murder.

124
00:06:33,018 --> 00:06:34,436
So, the obvious conclusion is...

125
00:06:34,853 --> 00:06:36,813
that Kira couldn't be one of them.

126
00:06:37,355 --> 00:06:38,398
However,

127
00:06:38,481 --> 00:06:41,526
what if he is one of these people
we've been watching?

128
00:06:41,985 --> 00:06:43,612
If he is, we have to assume

129
00:06:43,695 --> 00:06:46,197
that his psyche has reached
god-like proportions.

130
00:06:46,281 --> 00:06:49,284
Punishing evil-doers without
the slightest change of expression.

131
00:06:49,534 --> 00:06:52,120
It almost makes me want to believe
that Kira does not exist,

132
00:06:52,203 --> 00:06:54,915
that this is just
the wrath of a vengeful god.

133
00:06:55,540 --> 00:06:57,918
But that idea is completely absurd,

134
00:06:58,043 --> 00:07:01,338
to think that god would need a person's
face and name to kill them?

135
00:07:02,380 --> 00:07:03,423
No.

136
00:07:03,632 --> 00:07:05,091
These aren't acts of god.

137
00:07:05,550 --> 00:07:09,304
But someone very childish and immature
who wants to pretend they're god.

138
00:07:09,596 --> 00:07:10,889
That's what's going on here.

139
00:07:12,057 --> 00:07:15,310
The mass murderer who calls himself Kira
exists somewhere.

140
00:07:15,393 --> 00:07:17,145
I'm sure of it and I will catch him.

141
00:07:17,896 --> 00:07:21,107
But I can't count on Kira
making any mistakes.

142
00:07:21,274 --> 00:07:22,859
It doesn't matter how long we watch him,

143
00:07:22,984 --> 00:07:24,694
he's not gonna expose himself to us.

144
00:07:25,737 --> 00:07:27,489
So, what should I do?

145
00:07:28,823 --> 00:07:31,076
Ideally, I'd get to know him well enough

146
00:07:31,242 --> 00:07:33,370
that he'd admit to me that he was Kira

147
00:07:33,453 --> 00:07:35,080
and show me how he kills.

148
00:07:35,664 --> 00:07:37,457
Would that even be possible?

149
00:07:39,584 --> 00:07:41,294
[birds cawing]

150
00:07:41,962 --> 00:07:43,672
Hmm.

151
00:07:44,798 --> 00:07:48,677
Hey, Light. I've just checked
and all the cameras have been removed!

152
00:07:48,802 --> 00:07:50,971
All of them, every single one.

153
00:07:51,554 --> 00:07:53,765
Hello, are you listening to me?

154
00:07:56,393 --> 00:07:57,560
Hey, Light.

155
00:07:58,979 --> 00:08:00,730
Oh, good point.

156
00:08:00,814 --> 00:08:03,608
We still don't know if they've
removed all the wiretaps from the house.

157
00:08:04,776 --> 00:08:07,278
I suppose this means
I'm no longer a suspect.

158
00:08:07,779 --> 00:08:09,906
Everything is going as planned.

159
00:08:10,073 --> 00:08:12,450
But I'm sure L won't give up that easily.

160
00:08:12,701 --> 00:08:15,453
If he's still working
with the Japanese police,

161
00:08:15,912 --> 00:08:17,956
chances are my father is working with him.

162
00:08:18,248 --> 00:08:19,916
Or under him, anyway.

163
00:08:20,208 --> 00:08:21,459
If that's the case,

164
00:08:21,710 --> 00:08:25,046
I will have to use my father
to find out L's true identity

165
00:08:25,213 --> 00:08:26,464
and I'll eliminate him.

166
00:08:31,428 --> 00:08:33,013
Once I get rid of L,

167
00:08:33,638 --> 00:08:38,018
Kira will be one step closer
to becoming the god of the new world.

168
00:08:39,436 --> 00:08:40,812
[birds chirping]

169
00:08:41,021 --> 00:08:42,981
[Sachiko] Light, hurry up.
You don't wanna be late.

170
00:08:43,314 --> 00:08:44,524
Do your best.

171
00:08:44,691 --> 00:08:46,818
I know you don't need it, but good luck!
[chuckles]

172
00:08:46,943 --> 00:08:49,988
I really don't see why you two
are making such a big deal out of this.

173
00:08:54,701 --> 00:08:58,413
I'm relieved. We don't have to
deal with wiretaps in the house anymore.

174
00:08:58,580 --> 00:08:59,789
[Light] Well, it's nice to know

175
00:08:59,873 --> 00:09:02,250
that one cause of stress
was resolved before my exam.

176
00:09:02,792 --> 00:09:04,108
2007 TEST CENTER
FOR UNIVERSITY ADMISSIONS

177
00:09:04,233 --> 00:09:06,644
Once I get into university, I will have
a lot more room to act as Kira.

178
00:09:06,744 --> 00:09:09,382
Then I can focus on finding out
who L really is.

179
00:09:10,133 --> 00:09:12,802
You there! The exam will be starting
in ten minutes!

180
00:09:12,886 --> 00:09:14,137
So, you better hurry up!

181
00:09:15,138 --> 00:09:17,891
It's fine. I planned to get here
three minutes before the test.

182
00:09:17,974 --> 00:09:18,850
I hate waiting.

183
00:09:19,267 --> 00:09:20,602
I'm here too early.

184
00:09:20,685 --> 00:09:22,437
Well, well, confident.

185
00:09:25,356 --> 00:09:27,358
CIVICS EXAM PAPER

186
00:09:27,525 --> 00:09:29,527
-[bell tolls]
-And... begin.

187
00:09:36,367 --> 00:09:37,410
Hm?

188
00:09:47,462 --> 00:09:50,298
[professor] You there, student number 162.

189
00:09:50,465 --> 00:09:51,758
Sit properly in your chair.

190
00:09:51,883 --> 00:09:52,884
Hm?

191
00:10:44,811 --> 00:10:46,271
[Zellogi yawns]

192
00:10:46,479 --> 00:10:50,942
[Zellogi] It seems like a lot of Shinigami
are observing the human world lately.

193
00:10:51,067 --> 00:10:52,652
What's with that, anyway?

194
00:10:52,777 --> 00:10:55,989
It turns out that Ryuk
is being kept by a human.

195
00:10:56,781 --> 00:10:59,409
What's he thinking? Seriously.

196
00:10:59,534 --> 00:11:02,537
He's a disgrace to the pride of Shinigami.

197
00:11:02,745 --> 00:11:06,499
[Zellogi] No, I'm talking about the human
who's keeping Ryuk.

198
00:11:07,292 --> 00:11:09,043
Who would want him as a pet?

199
00:11:09,210 --> 00:11:11,337
Aren't pets supposed to be cute?

200
00:11:11,421 --> 00:11:13,089
[cackling]

201
00:11:13,173 --> 00:11:14,549
When you're right, you're right.

202
00:11:14,632 --> 00:11:17,218
So, what's the story
on this human, anyway?

203
00:11:17,385 --> 00:11:19,012
Is it a male or a female?

204
00:11:19,262 --> 00:11:20,638
Who knows?

205
00:11:20,722 --> 00:11:23,141
In that case, I think I better go
and take a closer look.

206
00:11:23,224 --> 00:11:24,142
Oh boy!

207
00:11:32,525 --> 00:11:34,068
[chattering]

208
00:11:47,665 --> 00:11:51,419
2007 TO-OH UNIVERSITY
ENTRANCE CEREMONY

209
00:11:54,130 --> 00:11:56,132
You're a college student now.

210
00:11:56,466 --> 00:11:57,759
That's kind of exciting.

211
00:11:57,884 --> 00:11:59,427
I'm filled with joy.

212
00:12:04,766 --> 00:12:06,559
Now for the freshman address,

213
00:12:06,809 --> 00:12:08,478
freshman representative,

214
00:12:08,686 --> 00:12:09,896
Light Yagami.

215
00:12:10,396 --> 00:12:11,397
[Light] Yes.

216
00:12:11,981 --> 00:12:13,608
Oh, wow.

217
00:12:14,150 --> 00:12:17,403
[man] And freshman representative,
Hideki Ryuga.

218
00:12:17,654 --> 00:12:18,905
[Ryuga] Oh, that's up here.

219
00:12:19,197 --> 00:12:21,324
Is that Hideki Ryuga, the pop idol?

220
00:12:21,449 --> 00:12:22,408
That guy?

221
00:12:22,533 --> 00:12:25,536
There's no way he's got the brains
to get into a school like To-oh.

222
00:12:25,828 --> 00:12:27,121
Yeah, you're right.

223
00:12:27,247 --> 00:12:29,999
He doesn't look anything
like the real Hideki Ryuga.

224
00:12:33,169 --> 00:12:36,089
I knew I'd be giving the address
with one other student.

225
00:12:36,297 --> 00:12:38,299
But I never expected this.

226
00:12:39,133 --> 00:12:41,427
I remember him from the exam center.

227
00:12:41,678 --> 00:12:44,347
He got into trouble
for sitting oddly in his desk.

228
00:12:45,056 --> 00:12:47,475
It seemed like he was off
in his own world.

229
00:12:52,355 --> 00:12:54,899
As all of us embark
on this new chapter of our lives...

230
00:12:54,983 --> 00:12:57,151
[student 1] The student who've
scored highest on the test

231
00:12:57,235 --> 00:12:58,945
is supposed to give the speech, right?

232
00:12:59,059 --> 00:13:01,364
[student 2] I guess both of them
must've had the high score this year.

233
00:13:01,484 --> 00:13:04,158
[student 1] I heard they both had
the perfect scores in all subjects.

234
00:13:04,284 --> 00:13:05,285
[student 2] Seriously?

235
00:13:05,368 --> 00:13:07,704
[student 1] It's hard to believe
there are people like that.

236
00:13:08,746 --> 00:13:10,707
I think I like the little one
on the right.

237
00:13:10,790 --> 00:13:12,959
What? You're so weird, Kyoko.

238
00:13:13,126 --> 00:13:14,377
Look at how he is dressed.

239
00:13:14,502 --> 00:13:15,378
[Kyoko] Mhmm.

240
00:13:20,133 --> 00:13:22,635
[student 1] Man, these two
are total opposites.

241
00:13:22,719 --> 00:13:23,636
[student 2] Yeah.

242
00:13:24,220 --> 00:13:26,264
[student 1] This one looks
like a sheltered genius

243
00:13:26,389 --> 00:13:28,308
who has been groomed for success
his whole life.

244
00:13:28,516 --> 00:13:29,726
But the other one...

245
00:13:29,934 --> 00:13:32,562
As we embark
on this new chapter in our lives...

246
00:13:32,645 --> 00:13:34,314
[student 1] There's something
not right about him.

247
00:13:34,397 --> 00:13:35,940
He's just freaking weird.

248
00:13:36,065 --> 00:13:38,693
[student 2] This guy must be
what they call a mad genius.

249
00:13:39,193 --> 00:13:42,238
[student 1] Coming to the To-oh
entrance ceremony dressed like that?

250
00:13:42,363 --> 00:13:43,865
Unbelievable!

251
00:13:44,032 --> 00:13:46,409
Either he's crazy,
or he's just toying with us.

252
00:13:46,576 --> 00:13:48,661
[Ryuga]
...freshman representative, Hideki Ryuga.

253
00:13:59,547 --> 00:14:02,592
Light?
Light Yagami?

254
00:14:02,884 --> 00:14:06,220
Your father is Chief Soichiro Yagami
of the NPA.

255
00:14:06,471 --> 00:14:09,807
Your respect for your father is matched
only by your strong sense of justice.

256
00:14:10,058 --> 00:14:11,642
Who the hell is this guy?

257
00:14:12,226 --> 00:14:15,063
You're planning to join the police agency
when you graduate.

258
00:14:15,355 --> 00:14:16,939
And you have already got experience,

259
00:14:17,065 --> 00:14:19,984
seeing as you've helped the police
solve a number of cases in the past.

260
00:14:20,234 --> 00:14:23,029
Now, you're showing an interest
in the Kira case.

261
00:14:23,946 --> 00:14:26,991
I'm impressed by your abilities
and your sense of justice.

262
00:14:27,325 --> 00:14:29,494
If you promise
not to tell anyone about this,

263
00:14:29,619 --> 00:14:32,580
I have important information
concerning the Kira investigation

264
00:14:32,747 --> 00:14:34,791
that I'd like to share with you.

265
00:14:35,083 --> 00:14:36,376
Where’s this coming from?

266
00:14:36,793 --> 00:14:38,086
And who is he?

267
00:14:38,544 --> 00:14:40,338
Is it safe to just ignore him?

268
00:14:40,588 --> 00:14:43,716
But... I wonder what this information
actually is.

269
00:14:44,842 --> 00:14:46,719
I won't tell anyone. What is it?

270
00:14:52,183 --> 00:14:54,018
I want to tell you I'm L.

271
00:14:58,606 --> 00:14:59,941
[Light] What? [gasps]

272
00:15:00,191 --> 00:15:01,401
There's no way.

273
00:15:01,734 --> 00:15:03,027
What's he talking about?

274
00:15:03,236 --> 00:15:05,780
If he really was L,
he would never admit to it.

275
00:15:06,197 --> 00:15:08,658
I thought this guy
was a bit strange but...

276
00:15:08,825 --> 00:15:10,118
This is pretty extreme.

277
00:15:10,660 --> 00:15:12,120
[groans] Stop.

278
00:15:12,537 --> 00:15:13,955
[puffs] This isn't good.

279
00:15:14,288 --> 00:15:15,665
Don't act surprised.

280
00:15:16,290 --> 00:15:18,668
On the off chance that he really is L,

281
00:15:18,835 --> 00:15:22,964
I have to act how Soichiro Yagami's son,
Light Yagami, would act in this situation.

282
00:15:23,423 --> 00:15:25,383
There'd be no reason for him to be afraid.

283
00:15:26,634 --> 00:15:28,511
If you are who you say you are,

284
00:15:28,636 --> 00:15:31,180
then you have nothing
but my respect and admiration.

285
00:15:31,389 --> 00:15:32,390
Thank you.

286
00:15:32,598 --> 00:15:35,143
The reason I chose to reveal
my identity to you

287
00:15:35,268 --> 00:15:37,145
is because I think
you could be of some help to us

288
00:15:37,228 --> 00:15:38,771
on the Kira investigation.

289
00:15:39,856 --> 00:15:41,315
Light Yagami.

290
00:15:41,691 --> 00:15:44,986
The likelihood that you are Kira
is just under five percent.

291
00:15:45,153 --> 00:15:46,112
Even so,

292
00:15:46,237 --> 00:15:48,698
something tells me
I'm not wrong to suspect you.

293
00:15:48,865 --> 00:15:50,408
But you're just too perfect.

294
00:15:50,491 --> 00:15:52,410
If you're Kira, I can't think of anything

295
00:15:52,535 --> 00:15:55,163
that would put more pressure on you
than this little scenario.

296
00:15:55,580 --> 00:15:56,956
[Ryuk chuckles]

297
00:15:57,165 --> 00:15:59,292
If this guy's really L, like he says,

298
00:15:59,459 --> 00:16:00,960
then consider me impressed.

299
00:16:01,335 --> 00:16:02,545
[Light] Indeed.

300
00:16:02,879 --> 00:16:04,380
If this guy really is L...

301
00:16:04,505 --> 00:16:07,216
No, even if he is not L, I...

302
00:16:07,467 --> 00:16:09,635
I-- I can't do anything to him.

303
00:16:10,178 --> 00:16:13,014
[Light breathing nervously]

304
00:16:15,558 --> 00:16:17,101
If what he's saying is true,

305
00:16:17,226 --> 00:16:20,313
it probably means he's already
shown his face to my father.

306
00:16:20,813 --> 00:16:21,856
What now?

307
00:16:22,440 --> 00:16:24,775
If he were to die
right after telling me who he was,

308
00:16:24,901 --> 00:16:26,903
it would only confirm their suspicions.

309
00:16:27,778 --> 00:16:32,033
Although it's obvious Hideki Ryuga
is nothing more than an absurd alias,

310
00:16:32,200 --> 00:16:33,701
it still complicates things.

311
00:16:33,951 --> 00:16:36,370
Even if I get lucky and it isn't an alias,

312
00:16:36,496 --> 00:16:39,999
if I try to kill him by simply
writing his name in the Death Note,

313
00:16:40,124 --> 00:16:43,211
I might accidentally picture the face
of Ryuga, the pop star,

314
00:16:43,419 --> 00:16:45,254
and end up killing him instead.

315
00:16:46,297 --> 00:16:48,090
If this guy doesn't die,

316
00:16:48,216 --> 00:16:50,092
he will know for a fact that I'm Kira.

317
00:16:52,011 --> 00:16:53,513
Is he really L?

318
00:16:53,888 --> 00:16:55,681
Does he already suspect that I'm Kira?

319
00:16:56,390 --> 00:16:58,434
It' hard to say how much he knows, but...

320
00:16:58,684 --> 00:17:00,394
I must be under suspicion.

321
00:17:00,645 --> 00:17:02,563
What other reason could he have

322
00:17:02,688 --> 00:17:05,816
for telling Soichiro Yagami's son
that he is L?

323
00:17:06,359 --> 00:17:08,402
Does this mean
that he's still suspicious of the people

324
00:17:08,528 --> 00:17:10,863
that Raye Penber was investigating
before he died?

325
00:17:11,531 --> 00:17:12,532
Even so,

326
00:17:12,657 --> 00:17:15,743
I still don't see why he would
reveal himself to me directly?

327
00:17:17,119 --> 00:17:19,330
I can't let him see any signs of distress.

328
00:17:19,872 --> 00:17:21,082
It's better if I just...

329
00:17:21,666 --> 00:17:23,334
clear my mind.

330
00:17:36,472 --> 00:17:40,601
[chuckles] I didn't think the ceremony
would be so interesting.

331
00:17:41,227 --> 00:17:42,853
[students chatter]

332
00:17:46,023 --> 00:17:47,066
[Ryuga] Hey, Light?

333
00:17:47,775 --> 00:17:48,943
You hear that?

334
00:17:49,151 --> 00:17:50,653
I think it's your new friend.

335
00:17:51,571 --> 00:17:53,155
-Uh... nice meeting you.
-No.

336
00:17:53,364 --> 00:17:54,699
The pleasure was mine.

337
00:17:58,327 --> 00:18:00,705
-What an amazing car.
-A limousine?

338
00:18:00,871 --> 00:18:03,291
Well, I'm sure I'll see you on campus.

339
00:18:03,499 --> 00:18:04,875
[Light] Yeah. Take care.

340
00:18:07,837 --> 00:18:10,089
[student 1] That kid must come from
some serious money.

341
00:18:10,256 --> 00:18:13,092
[student 2] Plus, he is at the top
of the class. Where is the justice?

342
00:18:31,527 --> 00:18:32,862
[music playing on TV]

343
00:18:33,070 --> 00:18:35,615
Hey, welcome home, Mister To-oh!

344
00:18:43,372 --> 00:18:44,707
[Ryuk] Huh? [chains jangling]

345
00:18:45,541 --> 00:18:47,835
[puffing]

346
00:18:48,044 --> 00:18:49,545
Damn it! He got me!

347
00:18:50,129 --> 00:18:51,756
Uh? What do you mean?

348
00:18:52,006 --> 00:18:53,257
Damn, L.

349
00:18:53,591 --> 00:18:55,551
I've never been so humiliated in my life!

350
00:18:56,135 --> 00:19:00,056
Ugh. Hey, why don't you just do
the Shinigami eye deal?

351
00:19:00,181 --> 00:19:02,391
Then you should have no problem
killing him, right?

352
00:19:02,558 --> 00:19:05,811
What good would Shinigami eyes do me
if this is just a trap?

353
00:19:06,020 --> 00:19:08,230
If I kill him
and it turns out he's not really L,

354
00:19:08,314 --> 00:19:10,941
then would be like announcing
to the real L that I'm Kira!

355
00:19:11,025 --> 00:19:12,943
Uh... Sorry.

356
00:19:13,694 --> 00:19:17,615
Don't think that Shinigami killing people
and humans killing people

357
00:19:17,823 --> 00:19:19,367
are the same thing because they're not.

358
00:19:20,451 --> 00:19:22,328
I want nothing more than to kill him,

359
00:19:22,411 --> 00:19:24,622
but if I do it,
it's like asking to get caught.

360
00:19:25,331 --> 00:19:29,460
Unfortunately, the Death Note can only
kill a person whose name is written in it.

361
00:19:29,835 --> 00:19:32,588
So, it's not like I can
arrange for someone else to kill him.

362
00:19:32,755 --> 00:19:35,591
It's inconvenient!
That's the flaw with the Death Note.

363
00:19:36,008 --> 00:19:39,011
Light is usually so calm,
but he snapped.

364
00:19:39,178 --> 00:19:40,596
This must be getting to him.

365
00:19:40,846 --> 00:19:42,890
At first, I thought
once I found out his name,

366
00:19:42,973 --> 00:19:45,309
I'll have him die in an accident
or kill himself.

367
00:19:45,726 --> 00:19:47,978
However, none of that will do me any good,

368
00:19:48,104 --> 00:19:51,065
unless I know with 100 percent certainty
that this guy is L.

369
00:19:51,315 --> 00:19:53,609
No. It's already too late
to do anything about it,

370
00:19:53,734 --> 00:19:56,237
since he's approached me
and introduced himself as L.

371
00:19:56,445 --> 00:19:58,072
It doesn't matter how sure I am.

372
00:19:58,280 --> 00:20:00,616
Regardless of the cause of death,
if L dies now,

373
00:20:00,700 --> 00:20:02,326
the police are going to suspect me.

374
00:20:03,494 --> 00:20:04,995
I underestimated him.

375
00:20:05,246 --> 00:20:07,248
I've never even considered the possibility

376
00:20:07,415 --> 00:20:10,543
that he would
reveal his identity to me on purpose.

377
00:20:12,712 --> 00:20:14,922
He could be telling all the suspects
the same thing.

378
00:20:15,047 --> 00:20:17,258
In fact, it doesn't even have to be him.

379
00:20:17,383 --> 00:20:19,385
He could have sent a double instead.

380
00:20:19,844 --> 00:20:22,680
For L, this strategy
acts as a solid defense

381
00:20:22,805 --> 00:20:24,724
and it allows him
to confront Kira directly.

382
00:20:24,974 --> 00:20:26,600
He can defend and attack.

383
00:20:27,143 --> 00:20:28,102
He got me.

384
00:20:28,227 --> 00:20:29,311
It was a good move.

385
00:20:30,187 --> 00:20:32,398
I'm sure I haven't seen the last of Ryuga.

386
00:20:32,523 --> 00:20:37,027
He will keep trying to move in on me,
playing the absent-minded genius

387
00:20:37,319 --> 00:20:39,989
and will pretend like nothing is going on.

388
00:20:42,324 --> 00:20:43,617
[chuckles]

389
00:20:44,201 --> 00:20:46,370
[laughing manically]

390
00:20:48,164 --> 00:20:49,039
Huh?

391
00:20:51,876 --> 00:20:53,252
This is perfect.

392
00:20:53,627 --> 00:20:55,671
There's no reason for me to be worried.

393
00:20:55,880 --> 00:20:59,049
After all, this is proof
that they don't have anything on me yet.

394
00:20:59,383 --> 00:21:02,553
So, this whole thing is nothing more
than a contest between L and me.

395
00:21:03,846 --> 00:21:05,139
A match of wits!

396
00:21:05,264 --> 00:21:07,975
On the surface we will be
two friendly classmates.

397
00:21:08,100 --> 00:21:09,268
But in reality,

398
00:21:09,477 --> 00:21:11,479
we will be investigating each other.

399
00:21:12,438 --> 00:21:13,773
This is interesting, Ryuga.

400
00:21:13,856 --> 00:21:15,441
If it's my friendship you want,

401
00:21:15,566 --> 00:21:16,942
I'll gladly accept it.

402
00:21:17,234 --> 00:21:18,944
In time I'll earn your trust.

403
00:21:19,612 --> 00:21:21,614
And once you've told me
what I want to know,

404
00:21:22,072 --> 00:21:24,200
there'll be no point keeping you alive.

405
00:21:24,450 --> 00:21:25,951
Then I will kill you...

406
00:21:26,535 --> 00:21:28,120
with my hands, if I have to.

407
00:21:30,247 --> 00:21:36,170
TO BE CONTINUED

408
00:21:41,675 --> 00:21:46,597
[theme music plays]
